               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Gadla Gabra Manfas Qǝddus “Vita of Gabra Manfas Qǝddus” (fols.
                     3ra-79vb)
 II) Taʾammǝra Gabra Manfas Qǝddus “Miracles of Gabra Manfas
                     Qǝddus”: 4 miracles in vita (fols. 80ra-88va)
 III) Taʾammǝra Gabra Manfas
                     Qǝddus “Miracles of Gabra Manfas Qǝddus”: 13 miracles post mortem (fols.
                     88va-105rb)
 
 Colophon.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1119DossierQMQ">Hagiographic Dossier of St Gabra Manfas Qǝddus</title>
                     <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.1">
                        <locus from="3ra" to="79vb"/>
                        <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1451GadlaG">Gadla Gabra Manfas Qǝddus (general record)</title>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.2">
                        <locus from="80ra" to="105rb"/>
                        <title>Taʾammǝra Gabra Manfas Qǝddus “Miracles of
                           Gabra Manfas Qǝddus”</title>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.2.1">
                           <locus from="80ra" to="88va"/>
                           <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT4077DersanG">Homily by Zenā Gabrǝʾel on Gabra Manfas Qǝddus; 4 miracles
                              in vita</title>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.2.2">
                           <locus from="88va" to="105rb"/>

                           <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT3977Taammer">Taʾammǝra Gabra Manfas Qǝddus “Miracles of Gabra Manfas Qǝddus”: 13 miracles</title>                    

                        </msItem>
                        <colophon xml:id="coloph1">
                           <locus target="#105rb"/>ተጽሕፈት፡ ዛቲ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ በ፲ወ፱፻፷፪፡ ዓ፡ ም፡ በዘመነ፡
                           መንግሥቱ፡ ለንጉሥነ፡ ኃይለ፡ ሥላሴ፡ ወሊቀ፡ ጳጳሳት፡ አባ፡ ባስልዮስ፡ ወብፁዕ፡ ጳጳስነ፡ አባ፡ ዮሐንስ። <note>The
                           colophon states that the Ms. was written in <date>1962 A.M (= 1969/1970 A.D.)</date> during
                           the reign of King Ḫāyla Śǝllāse (r. 1930-1975), tenure of Patriarch ʾabbā
                           Bāsǝlyos (1959-70) and Bishop ʾabbā Yoḥannǝs.</note> </colophon>
                     </msItem>
                     
                     
                  </msItem>
                  
